rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence, preferably
    from multiple sources or systems, to ensure foundational architecture stability.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be proposed by the system and explicitly
    accepted, rejected, or deferred by a human architect to maintain architectural
    integrity.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All heuristic-derived patterns must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure traceability and grounding in observed behavior.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
- id: rule-workflow-execution-model-compliance
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All runtime-native workflows must conform to the CAS Workflow Execution
    Model, specifically regarding the separation of concerns between orchestration,
    reasoning, and knowledge access.
  title: Rule Workflow Execution Model Compliance
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated only in structured
    decision records (ADR); all other representations must be derived from ADR.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the precedence model (Global > Project > Prompt) for resolving
    conflicts between rules originating from different sources within the system.
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of architecture items must be derived from decision
    status; items not marked 'accepted' cannot be considered 'DONE'.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-architecture-work-authority
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Work is the authoritative source of architectural planning
    state; all generated artifacts must derive status from this registry.
  title: Rule Architecture Work Authority
- id: rule-generated-artifacts-not-authoritative
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Generated governance artifacts (AEM, AID, Reports) summarize authoritative
    sources but must not become the authoritative source themselves.
  title: Rule Generated Artifacts Not Authoritative
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be merged or consolidated across different architectural
    layers to preserve clarity between governance, execution, and contracts.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) must reflect and never contradict
    the states and decisions recorded in ADRs.
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be persisted as structured ADRs before
    being reflected in AEM or other summary artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns must represent foundational architectural primitives rather
    than context-specific strategies or implementation details.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Establishes standard terminology and distinctions for Intent vs State,
    Decision vs System State, and lifecycle operations like promote and persist.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All decisions must be expressed using a structured YAML decision schema
    to enable machine processing and consistent interpretation.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be created as 'supporting' by default to ensure they
    are validated through evidence before being considered for 'core' status.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must utilize the shared Knowledge Workspace and avoid duplicating
    workspace-level governance structures or templates.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- compliance:
    enabled: true
  id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Enforces consistent mapping between pattern maturity stages (exploring,
    stable) and decision statuses (proposed, accepted, rejected).
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: A candidate signal is eligible for pattern promotion only if it satisfies
    mandatory recurrence, impact, reusability, and stability criteria.
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
summary:
  global_rules: 19
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 19
